uit access: Public."],["1990715-115","serviceberry","330 Massachusetts Rte 10, Northampton, MA 01060, USA","Serviceberry","Amelanchier",42.34699,-72.643155,"by the driveway to River Valley Coop, on the left corner as you enter Access: Public. Falling Fruit season: June-unknown.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1990715","2024-06-17 16:51:31 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["1806907-111","black-walnut","25 School St, Hatfield, MA 01038, USA","Black walnut","Juglans nigra",42.374125,-72.601963,"Two black walnut trees across from Smith Academy, directly west of single English Walnut Access: Private but overhanging. Falling Fruit season: October-October.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1806907","2021-10-27 05:22:30 UTC","Private but overhanging","private",false,"Falling Fruit access: Private but overhanging."],["1993878-72","ink-oak","105 Marian St, Northampton, MA 01060, USA","Oak","Quercus",42.356146,-72.645998,"Not sure of the type of oak but there are a LOT of oaks in the beginning of this Marian trail Falling Fruit season: September-November.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1993878","2024-08-27 19:48:11 UTC","","unknown",false,"Access unknown in Falling Fruit."],["2210892-114","apple","11 Wilder Pl, Florence, MA 01062, USA","Apple","Malus",42.33530033900558,-72.66831735243264,"I talked with Kate who lives at 11 Wilder. Very friendly. She says that she knows people in the neighborhood who come by to harvest the apples in October when they are ripe. Access: Private. Falling Fruit season: October-unknown.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/2210892","2025-08-15 05:00:21 UTC","Private","private",false,"Falling Fruit access: Private."],["2212474-114","apple","21 Sumner Ave, Florence, MA 01062, USA","Apple","Malus",42.335329169886855,-72.66429147553252,"2 small apple trees on the front lawn, very prolific producers of fruit! The people who live at the house don't use all of the apples and invite neighbors to pick some if you talk to them. Access: Private. Falling Fruit season: September-unknown.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/2212474","2025-09-17 05:00:20 UTC","Private","private",false,"Falling Fruit access: Private."],["1991110-114","apple","28 Keyes St, Northampton, MA 01062, USA","Apple","Malus",42.336498,-72.670539,"accessible right off the rail trail on the corner with Keyes St. I was harvesting the early drops today off the ground. some were easy to see in the grass, some i had to dig around in the taller plants by the base of the tree. Access: Public. Falling Fruit sea","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1991110","2024-07-14 19:35:26 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["1994472-114","apple","31 Bridge Rd, Northampton, MA 01062, USA","Apple","Malus",42.343664,-72.680197,"i think this tree might be a biennial producer, like apples every other year. at least with how it's being pruned (or not pruned). 2023 there were lots of apples. 2024 seemingly none. Anyways, all the apples just drop onto the ground. Access: Private. Falling ","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1994472","2024-09-12 00:05:18 UTC","Private","private",false,"Falling Fruit access: Private."],["2283544-111","black-walnut","5 Verona St, Florence, MA 01062, USA","Black walnut","Juglans nigra",42.33874532463658,-72.66254182275391,"i've never actually seen any nuts under the tree, maybe the landowners clean them away. Access: Private.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/2283544","2025-11-02 05:00:08 UTC","Private","private",false,"Falling Fruit access: Private."],["2283545-111","black-walnut","125 Straw Ave, Florence, MA 01062, USA","Black walnut","Juglans nigra",42.33904271753745,-72.66179616864777,"at least 2 big trees in the woods, great producers. Could be accessed from Meadowbrook housing complex or by walking down the path/ drainage ditch at the end of Straw Ave. There is an open flat area with